## REQUIREMENTS

- [Java 17](https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/javase/jdk17-archive-downloads.html)
- [Intellij IDEA](https://www.jetbrains.com/idea/)
- [Apache Kafka 3.9.0 Binary Scala 2.12](https://kafka.apache.org/community/downloads/)

### How to run:

1. Configure IntelliJ IDEA project to use Java 17.

    - Open the project.
    - Go to File → Project Structure (Ctrl+Alt+Shift+S on Windows/Linux).
    - Select Project on the left.
    - Set Project SDK → Java 17 and Project language level → 17 (or SDK default)
    
    - Go to Modules.
    - Select your module.
    - Under Dependencies, set Module SDK → Java 17 

2. Make sure kafka 3.9.0 binary Scala 2.12 is placed in C:/.

3. Open a cmd terminal and run the cmd:

```
cd C:\kafka
.\bin\windows\zookeeper-server-start.bat .\config\zookeeper.properties
```

4. Open a new cmd terminal and run the cmd:

```
cd C:\kafka_2.12-3.9.0
.\bin\windows\kafka-server-start.bat .\config\server.properties
```

5. Open "local-deployment/hosting-model-flask" folder and run:

```
pip install xgboost flask flask-cors joblib numpy pandas scikit-learn
python app.py
```
6. Now in IntelliJ IDEA terminal, run:

```
.\gradlew bootRun
```

7. Open a new vscode terminal in "data streaming" folder. Configure the SMTP with a gmail account and respective app password. Then run the cmd:

```
pip install python-dotenv
cd '.\streaming_data_into_model_from consumer\'
python stream_to_consumer.py
```

8. Open `http://localhost:8081` in your web browser.  